Sam wrote:

&gt; &quot;use-bdb-already-included&quot; seems like it would be a very useful option
&gt; for our project, but I can&#39;t find it in the web interface (even
&gt; building from CVS, using BdbFrontier, and showing expert settings).
&gt; How do I get this option?
&gt;
&gt; Thanks for your assistance.

If you are using HEAD, then default Frontier is BdbFrontier.  There is 
no option in this frontier because the bdb-based already-included is 
always enabled.

The above flag was added to the HeadQueuesFrontier, the previous default 
frontier.

Yours,
St.Ack

